<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate")%>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/static-pages.css">

<div class="index-container static-page">
    <h2 class="page-heading">Help & FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I list my place?</summary>
            <p>Log in, click "Add Listing" in the navbar, fill in the details, select the categories that apply, choose your accepted billing plans, and upload photos.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Can one listing offer multiple services?</summary>
            <p>Yes. A single shop (e.g., a cafe that also does Xerox) can select multiple categories when creating or editing its listing.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How does booking work?</summary>
            <p>Sending a booking request doesn't charge you anything. The owner reviews your request and either confirms or declines it. You can track the status under "My Bookings."</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I save a listing for later?</summary>
            <p>Click the heart icon on any listing card or its detail page. View all your saved listings under "Saved" in the navbar.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I manage requests for my own listings?</summary>
            <p>Go to "Bookings" → "Requests Received" in the navbar to approve or decline incoming requests.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is payment handled on UniNest?</summary>
            <p>Not yet — booking requests are confirmation-only for now. Payment is arranged directly with the owner.</p>
        </details>
    </div>

    <p class="static-footer-note">Still stuck? Reach out via the contact details on the listing page, or email us at support@uninest.example.</p>
</div>